 Alice - Five people arrested for public violence in Alice will appear in the local magistrate's court on Wednesday. "Five suspects, three women and two men aged between 23-55 were arrested on Tuesday and charged for public violence at Alice," said police spoksperson, Khaya Tonjeni. "This followed after the community embarked on a protest for water outage. "The five are expected to appear at Alice Magistrate's Court." Capt Tonjeni said that police have also facilitated a meeting between the community and local authorities to find amicable ways to solve the impasse. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 